README.md

Awesome

   A curated collection of text editing libraries, services, and resources
   for the web.

Rich-text editors using contenteditable

     * [https://github.com/basecamp/trix]Trix - Basecamp's rich text
       editor
     * [http://ckeditor.com/]CKEditor - Started back in 2003. Has both
       iframe and inline style rich-text editing
     * [https://github.com/neilj/Squire]Squire - HTML5 rich text editor
     * [http://prosemirror.net/]ProseMirror - From the maker of CodeMirror
     * [https://github.com/guardian/scribe]Scribe - From the
       [http://www.theguardian.com/]Guardian team
     * [http://quilljs.com/]Quill - Quill is a free, open source WYSIWYG
       editor built for the modern web
     * [http://summernote.org/]Summernote - Bootstrap dependent rich-text
       editor
     * [http://wysihtml.com/]wysihtml - Made by Voog
     * [http://etherpad.org/]Etherpad - Open Source online editor
       providing collaborative editing in really real-time
     * [http://www.tinymce.com/]TinyMCE - Used by much of the wordpress
       and drupal community
     * [http://jakiestfu.github.io/Medium.js/docs/]Medium.js - Warning:
       Not actually used by [https://medium.com/]Medium
     * [https://textbox.io/]Textbox.IO - From the makers of TinyMCE
     * [https://www.froala.com/wysiwyg-editor]Froala - A simple to use
       rich text editor, with mobile support, lots of examples, high
       performance and inline editing
     * [http://imperavi.com/redactor/]Redactor - Advanced, clean and
       smooth, Redactor Rich Text Editor offers an excellent immersive
       user experience
     * [https://github.com/ritzyed/ritzy]Ritzy - Collaborative web-based
       rich text editor
     * [http://www.alohaeditor.org/Content.Node/index.html]Aloha Editor -
       Open Source browser based html5 enabled rich text editor
     * [http://www.wymeditor.org/]WYMeditor - Open Source XHTML editor
       focusing on semantic markup
     * [http://dojotoolkit.org/]Dijit Editor - a Dojo-based rich text
       editor component
     * [http://yui.github.io/yui2/]YUI Rich Text Editor - a Yahoo! rich
       text editor component
     * [https://github.com/kindsoft/kindeditor]KindEditor - Open Source
       HTML editor
     * [https://github.com/bergie/hallo]Hallo - Simple rich text editor
       (contentEditable) for jQuery UI
     * [http://markitup.jaysalvat.com/home/]markitup - universal markup
       jQuery editor
     * [http://www.openwebware.com/]openwysiwyg - Free cross-browser
       WYSIWYG editor
     * [http://jqueryte.com/]tejQuery - Lightweight (19.5 KB) and very
       useful HTML editor
     * [http://alex-d.github.io/Trumbowyg/]Trumbowyg - light, translatable
       and customisable jQuery plugin
     * [http://nicedit.com/]NicEdit - Abandoned in 2012
     * [https://github.com/akzhan/jwysiwyg]jWYSIWYG - WYSIWYG jQuery
       Plugin
     * [http://alloyeditor.com/]Alloy - a modern WYSIWYG editor built on
       top of CKEDITOR
     * [http://facebook.github.io/draft-js/]Draft.js - a rich text editor
       framework for React

Code editors

     * [https://codemirror.net/]CodeMirror - CodeMirror is a versatile
       text editor implemented in JavaScript for the browser
     * [https://ace.c9.io/#nav=about]Ace - Ace is an embeddable code
       editor written in JavaScript
     * [http://www.cdolivet.com/editarea/editarea/exemples/exemple_full.ht
       ml]EditArea
     * [http://jakiestfu.github.io/Behave.js/]Behave.js - lightweight
       library for adding IDE style behaviors to plain text areas

Markdown editors

     * [https://github.com/evilstreak/markdown-js]markdown-js - A Markdown
       parser for javascript
     * [https://code.google.com/p/pagedown/wiki/PageDown]pagedown -
       PageDown is the JavaScript Markdown previewer used on Stack
       Overflow and the rest of the Stack Exchange network

Heuristic for contenteditable rich-text editors

   Editor should:
     * Be stable
     * Be open source
     * Handle soft breaks
     * Be able to manipulate styles on block level elements
     * Be able to manipulate styles on inline level elements
     * Be able to manipulate classes on block level elements
     * Be able to manipulate classes on inline level elements
     * Be able to alter custom attributes on block level elements
     * Be able to alter custom attributes on inline level elements
     * Cache the selection
     * Have iframing capabilities as well as inline mode capability
     * Change the tag type of nodes
     * Clear the format
     * Have a concise api
     * Support various module loaders
          + AMD & Common.js
     * Should have an organization backing the service and have a
       potential paid support plan
     * Should copy & paste from Microsoft word

